# Reflection

## What I Learned

Good API documentation should answer the most common developer questions before they are asked. Clear examples, well-defined parameters, and documented error responses make an API easier to integrate and reduce implementation mistakes.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

For larger APIs, I would include authentication requirements, rate limits, versioning information, and additional examples for different use cases.

